Package jdrasil.algorithms.lowerbounds

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Lowerbound<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The Lowerbound Interface describes a class that models an algorithm for computing a lower bound of the tree-width of a graph.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DegeneracyLowerbound<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    We call a Graph G=(V,E) d-degenerated if each subgraph H of G contains a vertex of maximal degree d.
    ImprovedGraphLowerbound<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The {k-neighbor / k-path}-improved graph \(H\) of a given graph \(G\) is obtained by adding an edge between all non adjacent vertices that have at least k {common neighbors / vertex disjoint paths}.
    MinorMinWidthLowerbound<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    It is a well known fact that for every minor H of G the following holds: \(tw(H) \le tw(G)\).
    PathImprovedGraph<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    Computes the k-path-improved-graph of the given graph, that is, the graph that is obtained by repeatedly adding edges between paris of non-adjacent vertices that have at least \(k\) vertex disjoint paths between them.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MinorMinWidthLowerbound.Algorithm
    The algorithm can use different strategies to select vertices (see Bodlaender and Koster: Treewidth Computations II).
